      "description": "This 997-generation Carrera S is a mechanically sound example of the 3.8L M97 flat-six platform. The naturally aspirated power plant features Variocam Plus valve timing and is mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle, offering an engaging, analog driving experience. This unit features Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) for optimized damping and four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers for consistent thermal management under load. The IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row ceramic upgrade, and the cooling system has been refreshed with a low-temp thermostat. While the finish shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain remains robust with excellent compression across all cylinders and a firm, communicative chassis.",
